The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of a graph problem, specifically the connected version of the vertex cover problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory. The paper focuses on planar graphs, which are a well-studied class of graphs in computer science, and provides a new kernelization algorithm for this problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves complexity theory and graph theory, which could also place it in the sub-categories cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
